Why Listen to Me?
17:10

This is an overview lecture for the course, starting with things that mainstream economics failed to see coming, and including critical commentaries on mainstream economics from mainstream economists themselves. On that note, I've attached two excellent and very readable critiques by "Nobel" Prize winners Robert Solow and Paul Romer.

Resources
Robert Solow's "Dumb and Dumber"
Paul Romer's "Trouble with Macro"
